#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:1
msgid "Caddy Reverse Proxy"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:3
msgid ""
"Caddy handles TLS termination, automatic Let's Encrypt certificate "
"provisioning, and reverse-proxy routing for all VM-hosted services (Keycloak "
"ACC, Keycloak PROD, Operaton)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:7
msgid "Repository structure"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:9
msgid ""
"deployment/vm/caddy/\n"
"└── Caddyfile       # Reverse proxy configuration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:14
msgid ""
"The `Caddyfile` is version-controlled but must be copied to the VM and "
"loaded by the Caddy container. It is **not** committed with secrets."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:18
msgid "Caddyfile"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:20
msgid ""
"acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl {\n"
"    reverse_proxy keycloak-acc:8080\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"keycloak.open-regels.nl {\n"
"    reverse_proxy keycloak-prod:8080\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"operaton.open-regels.nl {\n"
"    reverse_proxy operaton:8080\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:34
msgid ""
"Caddy automatically provisions and renews Let's Encrypt certificates for all "
"listed domains. HTTP requests are automatically redirected to HTTPS."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:38
msgid "Retrieving the Caddyfile from a running VM"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:40
msgid ""
"If the Caddyfile on the VM has diverged from the version in the repository, "
"retrieve the live version and commit it:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:42
msgid ""
"ssh user@open-regels.nl \"docker exec caddy cat /etc/caddy/Caddyfile\" \\\n"
"  > deployment/vm/caddy/Caddyfile"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:47
msgid ""
"Review the diff before committing — the VM copy is authoritative for any "
"manual changes made outside of the normal deploy flow."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:51
msgid "Deploying Caddy"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:53
msgid ""
"ssh user@open-regels.nl\n"
"mkdir -p ~/caddy"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:58
msgid "Copy the Caddyfile to the VM:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:60
msgid "scp deployment/vm/caddy/Caddyfile user@open-regels.nl:~/caddy/"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:64
msgid "Create `~/caddy/docker-compose.yml` on the VM:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:66
msgid ""
"version: '3.8'\n"
"services:\n"
"  caddy:\n"
"    image: caddy:2-alpine\n"
"    container_name: caddy\n"
"    ports:\n"
"      - \"80:80\"\n"
"      - \"443:443\"\n"
"    volumes:\n"
"      - ./Caddyfile:/etc/caddy/Caddyfile\n"
"      - caddy-data:/data\n"
"      - caddy-config:/config\n"
"    restart: always\n"
"    networks:\n"
"      - npm-network\n"
"\n"
"volumes:\n"
"  caddy-data:\n"
"  caddy-config:\n"
"\n"
"networks:\n"
"  npm-network:\n"
"    external: true"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:92
msgid "Start Caddy:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:94
msgid ""
"cd ~/caddy\n"
"docker compose up -d\n"
"docker compose logs -f caddy    # verify certificate provisioning"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:100
msgid "Caddy is ready when you see: `certificate obtained successfully`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:104
msgid "Adding a new domain"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:106
msgid "To expose a new VM service through Caddy:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:108
msgid "Add a DNS A record pointing the new subdomain to the VM's public IP"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:109
msgid "Add a new block to the `Caddyfile`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:109
msgid ""
"newservice.open-regels.nl {\n"
"    reverse_proxy newservice-container:8080\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:115
msgid "Copy the updated `Caddyfile` to the VM and reload:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:115
msgid ""
"scp deployment/vm/caddy/Caddyfile user@open-regels.nl:~/caddy/\n"
"ssh user@open-regels.nl 'docker exec caddy caddy reload --config /etc/caddy/"
"Caddyfile'"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:123
msgid "Docker network"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:125
msgid ""
"All VM containers communicate over a shared Docker network named `npm-"
"network`. Caddy resolves Keycloak and Operaton by their container names "
"(`keycloak-acc`, `keycloak-prod`, `operaton`) within this network. Ensure "
"all containers specify `networks: npm-network` in their `docker-compose.yml`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:129
msgid "Security hardening"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:131
msgid "Security headers"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:133
msgid ""
"Add a reusable `import` snippet to apply security headers to all proxied "
"services:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:135
msgid ""
"(security_headers) {\n"
"    header {\n"
"        Strict-Transport-Security \"max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; "
"preload\"\n"
"        X-Content-Type-Options \"nosniff\"\n"
"        X-Frame-Options \"SAMEORIGIN\"\n"
"        X-XSS-Protection \"1; mode=block\"\n"
"        Referrer-Policy \"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\"\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl {\n"
"    import security_headers\n"
"    reverse_proxy keycloak-acc:8080\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"keycloak.open-regels.nl {\n"
"    import security_headers\n"
"    reverse_proxy keycloak-prod:8080\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"operaton.open-regels.nl {\n"
"    import security_headers\n"
"    reverse_proxy operaton:8080\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:162
msgid "Rate limiting"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:164
msgid "To protect Keycloak login from brute-force attempts at the proxy level:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:166
msgid ""
"acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl {\n"
"    import security_headers\n"
"    rate_limit {\n"
"        zone acc_keycloak {\n"
"            key {remote_host}\n"
"            events 100\n"
"            window 1m\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"    reverse_proxy keycloak-acc:8080\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:180
msgid ""
"Note: Keycloak's built-in brute-force protection (5 failed attempts → "
"lockout) is configured in the realm settings and operates independently of "
"Caddy rate limiting."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:184
msgid "Verifying SSL certificates"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:186
msgid ""
"# Check certificate expiry for each domain\n"
"echo | openssl s_client -servername acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl \\\n"
"  -connect acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl:443 2>/dev/null | openssl x509 -"
"noout -dates\n"
"\n"
"echo | openssl s_client -servername keycloak.open-regels.nl \\\n"
"  -connect keycloak.open-regels.nl:443 2>/dev/null | openssl x509 -noout -"
"dates\n"
"\n"
"echo | openssl s_client -servername operaton.open-regels.nl \\\n"
"  -connect operaton.open-regels.nl:443 2>/dev/null | openssl x509 -noout -"
"dates"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:198
msgid ""
"Caddy stores certificates in the `caddy-data` volume and renews them "
"automatically ~30 days before expiry. No manual intervention is required "
"unless DNS or the VM IP changes."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:202
msgid "Metrics and monitoring"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:204
msgid ""
"Caddy exposes a metrics/admin endpoint on port 2019 (localhost only, not "
"exposed to internet):"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:206
msgid ""
"# From the VM\n"
"curl http://localhost:2019/metrics"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:211
msgid "To follow access logs:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:213
msgid ""
"docker logs -f caddy\n"
"\n"
"# Filter for a specific domain\n"
"docker logs caddy 2>&1 | grep \"acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl\""
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:222
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:224
msgid ""
"**Service returns 502 Bad Gateway** — Caddy can reach the domain but can't "
"reach the backend container. Check:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:226
msgid "Container is running: `docker ps`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:227
msgid ""
"Container is on `npm-network`: `docker network inspect npm-network | grep "
"<container-name>`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:228
msgid ""
"Container name in Caddyfile matches exactly: `docker ps --format '{{.Names}}"
"'`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:230
msgid "**Certificate not provisioning** — Check that:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:232
msgid ""
"DNS A record for the domain points to the VM's public IP: `dig "
"acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:233
msgid "Ports 80 and 443 are open on the VM: `sudo ufw status`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:234
msgid ""
"Caddy logs for ACME errors: `docker logs caddy | grep -i \"acme\\"
"|certificate\\|error\"`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:236
msgid "**Validate Caddyfile syntax before reloading:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Ccaddy.md:238
msgid "docker exec caddy caddy validate --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile"
msgstr ""
